{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17521393","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17521393"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:33:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:33:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13604"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13604"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.05,0.64,0.03,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6217"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105681"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6217","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6217"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13604"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88132"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"106"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"12480"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15524"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35649"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38492"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42899"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105681","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/105681"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a one-week history of palpitations and shortness of breath on exertion. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 100/min and blood pressure is 140/85 mmHg. Auscultation of the heart reveals no murmurs, and lung fields are clear. His CHADS-VA score is 4. An electrocardiogram is performed (Image 1). You decide anticoagulation is clinically indicated.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["24-hour Holter monitor","Troponin","Echocardiogram","Chest X-ray","Cardiac stress test"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eechocardiogram\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate next step in the investigation of a new diagnosis of atrial fibrillation. It is essential to assess for the presence of structural heart disease, including:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELeft atrial size and function\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELeft ventricular function\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EValvular pathology (especially mitral stenosis or regurgitation)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPresence of thrombus (in transoesophageal echo) \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EValvular conditions such as mitral stenosis may not only can contribute to atrial fibrillation but also will dictate the type of anticoagulation. Currently only warfarin is indicated for patients with moderate or more mitral stenosis, for all other valve conditions a DOAC is indicated in the first instance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003E24-hour Holter monitor\u003C/strong\u003E is useful for assessing the burden of atrial fibrillation over a 24-hour period but does not provide information on structural heart disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETroponin\u003C/strong\u003E is a cardiac biomarker used to detect myocardial injury. It may be elevated in some cases of atrial fibrillation, particularly if there is rapid ventricular response or underlying coronary artery disease. However, as there are no symptoms of typical cardiac chest pain or ECG findings of cardiac ischaemia in this case, a troponin would be inappropriate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Echest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E can provide information on heart size and lung pathology but is less specific than an echocardiogram for evaluating heart structure and function. While a chest x-ray may be considered to exclude other causes of shortness of breath, the patient\u0027s clear lung fields on examination point against this.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ecardiac stress test\u003C/strong\u003E is used to evaluate for coronary artery disease and is not the first-line investigation for a new diagnosis of atrial fibrillation when assessing for structural heart disease. While it may be considered later in the workup, particularly if there are concerns about underlying ischemia, an echocardiogram should be performed first to assess cardiac structure and function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["For patients with a new diagnosis of atrial fibrillation, an echocardiogram should be performed to assess for the presence of valvular conditions and to assess left atrial and ventricular size and function."],"references":["Joglar JA, Chung MK, Armbruster AL, Benjamin EJ, Chyou JY, Cronin EM, et al. 2023 ACC/AHA/ACCP/HRS Guideline for the Diagnosis and Management of Atrial Fibrillation: A Report of the American College of Cardiology/American Heart Association Joint Committee on Clinical Practice Guidelines. Circulation. 2024;149(1):e1-e156. Available at: https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/CIR.0000000000001193","Hindricks G, Potpara T, Dagres N, et al. 2020 ESC Guidelines for the diagnosis and management of atrial fibrillation developed in collaboration with the European Association for Cardio-Thoracic Surgery (EACTS). European Heart Journal. 2021;42(5):373-498. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32860505/","Kotecha D, Lam CSP, Van Veldhuisen DJ, Van Gelder IC, Voors AA, Rienstra M. Heart Failure With Preserved Ejection Fraction and Atrial Fibrillation: Vicious Twins. Journal of the American College of Cardiology. 2016;68(20):2217-2228. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27855811/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88132"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13604"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20923"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20923"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wPBfVKyBzZb5TVx2BYaRnJvMHIxkQ4.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wPBfVKyBzZb5TVx2BYaRnJvMHIxkQ4.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":414}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88132"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-11T15:17:26+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-11T15:18:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6217"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105681"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","syno